Class CalcMap<K,V,D extends Data>

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Data, DataListener, DataMap<K,V>, View
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DefaultGroupedTable, GroupedSeries

    public abstract class CalcMap<K,V,D extends Data>
extends AbstractMapView<K,V,D>
    Base class for creating DataMaps that are optionally calculated from another Data source. If input data is provided then change events on the data trigger a recalculation of this map. Subclasses must implement #update()).
    Author:
    O. J. Coleman

        public void update(DataEvent cause)

      • keys

        public DataSeries<K> keys()
        Description copied from interface: DataMap
        Get a view of the keys in this map. The keys will have the same order as the values provided by DataMap.values(). Changes to this map will be reflected in the returned series.

      • values

        public DataSeries<V> values()
        Description copied from interface: DataMap
        Get a view of the values in this map. The values will have the same order as the keys provided by DataMap.keys(). Changes to this map will be reflected in the returned series.
